content: Presidential election in Singapore Indirect presidential elections were held in [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) on 6 November 1974. The election took place during a sitting of Parliament on 6 November 1974 where 59 members were present and 6 members were absent. Prime Minister [Lee Kuan Yew](/wiki/Lee_Kuan_Yew) nominated Benjamin Sheares for a second term as president. Sheares was unanimously re-elected by Parliament as president.
